      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Delay until next spring has &C.\nCured in the immense proposition\nto pave the streets of the city from\nMonroe street to Occur d'Alene\npark and from the Spokane river to\nFourth avenue with asphalt. The\nestimated cost of the improvement\nis $559,000. and the assessed value\nof the property affected Is over\n100000.\n\n\nThe motion to delay the improve\nment was made at the meeting Of\nthe city council last night by Coun-\nGilman Jacob Schiller, who stated\nthat the people affected by the i'm\nprovement had become divided as\nto the character of the material to\nbe used, and for other reasons. and\nthat a remonstrance had been start\ned against the work. Mr.. Schiller\nserved notice that he will insist on\nthe work going ahead the first thing\nIn the spring."
    }
